      <section id="main_content" class="inner">
    <h3><a id="About" class="anchor" href="#About" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Welcome to EpicMode</h3>
		<p>EpicMode is an open source project to design clothing from measurements to manufacturing using 3D tools.</p>
		
		<p>EpicMode is a disruptive project for the 2nd largest industry ($2.3Trillion) on the planet. It is the beginning of a new stack of tools to rebuild and recreate the fashion industry.  We can enable change by redefining the process. Open source tools designed to implement the Next Economy for the world's second largest industry. Change won't happen from within in the conservative fashion industry. Fashion is the 2nd largest industry in the world, which also makes it the the 2nd largest polluter in the world, surpassed only by the oil industry. Sadly it is also the largest user of child and indentured slave labor in the world. New players, processes, and workflows are required to create change.</p>
		
		<p>We have team members in China, Taiwan, Vietnam, Ukraine, France, Germany, England, and USA. We have presented at conferences and held workshops in Singapore, Hong Kong, Shenzhen, Austria, Belgium, Germany, England, and Canada.</p>
		
<p>The Fashion and Textile industry is the second largest industry, the second largest polluter, and the greatest user of indentured slaves and child labor in the world. Change will not happen from within in this conservative industry.  New players, tools, and work flows at the design and manufacturing level are required to implement change.</p> 

<p>Valentina open source pattern drafting software (www.valentina-project.org) enables profits for small batch and custom-size garment by making 'smart' patterns, where each pattern fits any body of any size in any market. Valentina brings 21st century technology and engineering principles into garment design, and improves garment fit by removing ethnic and gender biases. By introducing parametric design, open data formats, open source code, and collaborative culture to the fashion industry, Valentina can remove artificial barriers to entry and enable higher profits. Valentina can make a difference in the lives of women around the world.</p> 
 
<p>The Valentina development team would like to enable persons in underdeveloped communities and on underdeveloped continents to become participants in this industry. Independent designers anywhere can create garment profitably by utilizing any manufacturer through the use of open data formats. By enabling independent garment manufacturing for single and small batch sizes Valentina also enables demand for small and artisanal textiles from small and medium sized textile mills around the globe. Healthy  and textile districts with smaller working communities can reduce the levels of child and indentured slave labor used in garment manufacturing.</p>  

<p>As an additional goal for Valentina, educators from Lebanon and Egypt have requested an Arabic translation of Valentina.  They indicated that learning pattern drafting software with Valentina would be allowed in conservative religious communities in the Middle East, where women are not normally taught math or given access to computers.</p> 

<div><p>Goals
    <ul>
        <li>1. introduce custom fit garment to global markets </li>
        <li>2. create profits for small batch sizes</li> 
        <li>3. implement eco-fashion and slow-fashion to reduce waste</li> 
        <li>4. rebuild local garment districts</li> 
        <li>5. revive small textile mills </li>
        <li>6. reduce slavery and child labor</li>
        <li>7. enable garment production for underserved markets</li> 
        <li>8. reintroduce regional and local fashion styles</li>
        <li>9. invite women in all cultures to become open source contributosr</li> 
        <li>10. teach math and computer literacy to women in conservative cultures </li>
        <li>11. enable any designer to work with any manufacturer around the globe</li>
       </ul>
</p></div>

