<h3>Development</h3>

<p>Valentina concluded a 3D Design Sprint, sponsored by Adidas, during the Libre Graphics Meeting at the University of Westminster in London, April 13-18, 2016. The meeting determined the architecture and roadmap for adding 3D Character, 3D Measurement, 3D Pattern, and 3D Visualization features.</p>

<p>The University of Pisa, CNR-ISTI, MeshLab (www.meshlab.js), and MakeHuman (www.makehuman.org) are working together to provide Valentina's 3D mesh, surface reconstruction, measurements, and animation.</p>

<p>The University of Parma is currently developing additional Valentina pre-processing features.</p>

<p>Georgia Institute of Technology's Institute for People and Technology is in the early stages of defining a program for Valentina 3D Visualization.</p>

<p>The Arte Diez (artediez.es) charter school in Madrid is developing a Valentina training manual for use in their design program.</p>

<h3>Call for partners</h3>

<p>Valentina is seeking university partners to develop 2D and 3D graphics features, provide project management, design the user interface, manage translations, create an international website, and develop international educational materials. </p>


